# Diabetes Dataset Analysis Using Python, Pandas, and EDA

## Project Overview

This project is part of the Week 1 Data Science Foundations assignment. The aim of the project is to analyze the Diabetes Dataset using Python, Pandas, Matplotlib, and Seaborn.

The project includes:
- Data loading and inspection
- Data cleaning
- Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
- Data visualization
- AI co-pilot workflow explanation
- Data storytelling

---

# Dataset Used

Diabetes Dataset from Kaggle:

https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/akshaydattatraykhare/diabetes-dataset

---

# Technologies Used

- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
- Google Colab

---

# Tasks Completed

## TASK 1 — AI Co-pilot Loop
- Explained the AI co-pilot workflow
- Wrote and explained a good AI prompt

## TASK 2 — Diabetes + Pandas
Performed:
- `head()`
- `info()`
- `describe()`

Answered:
- Number of diabetic patients
- Average glucose level
- Female patients above age 40
- Average BMI grouped by outcome
- Rows removed after cleaning glucose values

---

## TASK 3 — Five Chart Types

Created:
- Histogram
- Scatter Plot
- Bar Chart
- Box Plot
- Line Chart

Re-created all charts using Seaborn styling and compared both versions.

---

## TASK 4 — Data Story

Investigated:
1. Does glucose level affect diabetes outcome?
2. Is BMI linked to diabetes outcome?
3. Which age group has the highest diabetes rate?

Included:
- Charts
- Findings
- Future exploration ideas

---

# Key Insights

- Patients with higher glucose levels were more likely to have diabetes.
- Higher BMI values appeared more common among diabetic patients.
- Middle-aged adults showed a higher diabetes occurrence in the dataset.

